# Loophacka

React + TypeScript SPA built with Vite.

## Stack

- React 19 (functional components, hooks)
- TypeScript (strict)
- Vite 8
- Oxlint for linting
- CSS modules via colocated `.css` files (no CSS-in-JS unless requested)

## Project structure

```
src/
  main.tsx       # entry point
  App.tsx        # root component
  index.css      # global styles
  assets/        # static imports (images, svgs)
public/          # static files served as-is
```

## Conventions

- Use functional components and hooks; avoid class components
- Prefer named exports for utilities/hooks; default export for page-level components is fine
- Colocate component styles in a sibling `.css` file (e.g. `App.css`)
- Import assets from `src/assets/`; reference public assets with absolute paths (e.g. `/icons.svg`)
- Use explicit `type="button"` on non-submit buttons
- Keep components focused; extract reusable logic into custom hooks in `src/hooks/`
- Add new components under `src/components/` as the app grows

## TypeScript

- Avoid `any`; prefer explicit types for props and return values
- Use `interface` for component props, `type` for unions and utilities
- Non-null assertions (`!`) only when the value is guaranteed (e.g. `getElementById('root')`)

## Commands

```bash
npm run dev      # dev server at http://localhost:5173
npm run build    # typecheck + production build
npm run lint     # oxlint
npm run preview  # preview production build
```

## Agent guidelines

- Minimize scope: only change what the task requires
- Match existing code style (no semicolons in imports, single quotes)
- Do not add dependencies without being asked
- Do not commit unless explicitly requested
- Do not create markdown docs unless requested
- Run `npm run build` after significant changes to verify the project compiles
